    "body": "> Maybe also worth methioning: I checked the size of my contract's bytecode and it should be ~16kb, well under the 24kb limit of EIP170.\r\n\r\nThis is a bit confusing. The EIP170 limit is about the size of the resulting bytecode. But if the deployment code spends a lot of gas (say, there's a loop in the constructor or whatever) then you might hit #3420. This is, of course, a bug in Hardhat.",
